# TASK ARCHIVING

> **TL;DR:** Archive completed tasks with results, testing, lessons, and doc updates.

## STRUCTURE
```
docs/archive/
└── completed_tasks.md
```

## ARCHIVE FORMAT
```
## Task: [Name] (v1.0)
Updated: YYYY-MM-DD

### Results
[Implementation details]

### Testing
[Test coverage]

### Lessons
[Key insights]

### Docs
[Updated files]
```

## CROSS-LINKS

### progress.md
```
## Completed
- [Task] - YYYY-MM-DD, [archive](../docs/archive/completed_tasks.md#task-name-v10)
```

### activeContext.md
```
## Recent
- [Task] done. Next: [Next Task]
```

## CHECKLIST
- [ ] Archive exists
- [ ] Entry includes:
  - Name + v1.0
  - Date (YYYY-MM-DD)
  - All sections
- [ ] Links updated:
  - progress.md
  - activeContext.md
  - tasks.md

## SECTIONS

### Results
- Features added
- Changes made
- Tech used

### Testing
- Methods used
- Coverage
- Edge cases

### Lessons
- What worked
- Challenges
- Future tips

### Docs
- Files updated
- Major changes
- New patterns
